# ==============================================
# AfterMeeting - Environment Variables Template
# ==============================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values
# For Vercel deployment, add these as Environment Variables
# ==============================================

# Supabase Configuration (Required)
# Get these from your Supabase project settings
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ==============================================
# SUPABASE SECRETS (Configure in Supabase Dashboard)
# ==============================================
# These are NOT .env variables - they are Supabase Edge Function secrets
# Go to: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > Edge Functions > Secrets
#
# SUPABASE_URL           - Auto-configured by Supabase
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY      - Auto-configured by Supabase
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY - Auto-configured by Supabase
#
# External API Keys (Required for full functionality):
# OPENAI_API_KEY         - Required for audio transcription and AI analysis
# RESEND_API_KEY         - Required for sending emails
# RESEND_FROM            - Email sender address (e.g., "AfterMeeting <no-reply@yourdomain.com>")
#
# Optional Secrets:
# RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET  - For email event tracking (optional)
# ==============================================

# ==============================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST
# ==============================================
# 1. Set up Supabase project and copy URL/Keys
# 2. Configure Supabase Edge Function Secrets:
#    - OPENAI_API_KEY
#    - RESEND_API_KEY
#    - RESEND_FROM
# 3. Verify email domain in Resend dashboard
# 4. Create storage bucket 'audio-recordings' (auto-created via migration)
# 5. Run all database migrations
# 6. Configure custom domain (optional)
# ==============================================